==English==
===Etymology===
A part-translation of German [[Erlkönig]] literally ‘alder-king’, a mistranslation of Danish [[ellerkonge]] ‘king of the elves’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'ɜ:lkɪŋ/

===Noun===
{{en-noun|erl-king|erl-kings}}
# in German mythology, a [[giant]] who preys on [[children]]

===Alternative forms===
* [[erlking]]